Package: hotteR
Type: Package
Title: Hottest 100 Countdown and Triple J Analysis in R
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
  person("Trent", "Henderson", email = "trent.henderson1@outlook.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
  person("Joy", "Horng", email = "joy.horng@nousgroup.com.au", role = "aut")
  )
Maintainer: Trent Henderson <trent.henderson1@outlook.com>
Description: Automates extraction of @triplejplays data and Hottest 100 Countdown 
             analysis and provides high-level analysis and data visualisation of
             the extracted data. Some functions in the package access the Twitter 
             API and thus require appropriate credentials to be available in the 
             R Environment prior to running. The 'twitteR' package provides a 
             useful setup_twitter_oauth() function for this.
BugReports: https://github.com/hendersontrent/hotteR/issues
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: 
    dplyr, 
    magrittr,
    ggplot2,
    tidyr,
    stringr,
    glue,
    data.table,
    ggpubr,
    janitor,
    rtweet,
    RSelenium
Suggests:
    scales
